Paper: hep-th/9707144

Date: 1997-07-16

Title: On the Bound States in a Non-linear Quantum Field Theory of a Spinor

Field with Higher DerivativesAuthors: A.D. Mitov, M.N. Stoilov and D.Ts. Stoyanov

Comments: 14 pages, no figures, LaTeX

Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A14 (1999) 1651-1662

We consider a model of quantum field theory with higher derivatives for aspinor field with quartic selfinteraction. With the help of the Bethe-Salpeterequation we study the problem of the two particle bound states in the "chain"approximation. The existence of a scalar bound state is established.